WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.000
<i>[This program is suitable
for viewers ages 15 and up.]</i>

2
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Subtitles by DramaFever

3
00:00:24.250 --> 00:00:26.540
<i>[Episode 5]</i>

4
00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:29.043
Are you asleep, Mom?

5
00:00:30.652 --> 00:00:32.508
I'm not asleep.

6
00:00:33.155 --> 00:00:36.097
But I don't want to move.

7
00:00:36.097 --> 00:00:38.408
I feel the same way.

8
00:00:41.011 --> 00:00:43.271
It'll probably be cold outside.

9
00:00:43.271 --> 00:00:44.745
Right?

10
00:00:45.310 --> 00:00:47.430
It's warm here.

11
00:00:47.430 --> 00:00:49.364
Right?

12
00:00:49.834 --> 00:00:51.662
Yeah.

13
00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:54.304
You know that story of the boy and girl

14
00:00:54.304 --> 00:00:57.990
who were wandering around in a forest

15
00:00:57.990 --> 00:01:03.094
and discovered a house made of snacks?

16
00:01:03.094 --> 00:01:05.191
This reminds me of that.

17
00:01:05.191 --> 00:01:07.165
You mean Hansel and Gretel?

18
00:01:07.165 --> 00:01:09.555
You know how I almost screamed

19
00:01:09.555 --> 00:01:12.177
when they found that house
made of snacks?

20
00:01:12.177 --> 00:01:14.206
Because I was so happy?

21
00:01:15.986 --> 00:01:18.283
Are you saying that
we're like Hansel and Gretel?

22
00:01:18.283 --> 00:01:21.030
We had the book with that
story in it, at school

23
00:01:21.030 --> 00:01:24.578
but the page where they found
the house made of snacks

24
00:01:24.578 --> 00:01:27.007
was all worn out, since it was
the most frequently read.

25
00:01:27.564 --> 00:01:31.263
Do you know what happens after that?

26
00:01:31.896 --> 00:01:33.924
They almost die.

27
00:01:33.924 --> 00:01:36.004
Because that house
belongs to a witch.

28
00:01:36.004 --> 00:01:37.974
Really?

29
00:01:37.974 --> 00:01:40.337
I didn't get to that part yet.

30
00:01:40.337 --> 00:01:43.370
It's a house that a witch made
out of snacks

31
00:01:43.370 --> 00:01:45.932
so that she could lure
young children in.

32
00:01:46.493 --> 00:01:47.876
Oh no.

33
00:01:47.876 --> 00:01:49.588
But they don't die.

34
00:01:49.588 --> 00:01:52.247
The kids kill the witch,
and run away.

35
00:01:52.247 --> 00:01:53.592
What about the house?

36
00:01:53.592 --> 00:01:55.592
Do they eat it all?

37
00:01:56.424 --> 00:01:57.867
Are you hungry?

38
00:01:58.576 --> 00:02:00.025
Yes.

39
00:02:00.664 --> 00:02:03.050
We have to get you
something to eat.

40
00:02:05.236 --> 00:02:07.319
You need to eat so that
you can take your medicine.

41
00:02:17.435 --> 00:02:20.296
This footage is from
December 16th at 10:45 p.m.

42
00:02:20.296 --> 00:02:22.436
on the second floor
of Baek Island Mart.

43
00:02:23.018 --> 00:02:24.683
What, you can't see it again?

44
00:02:24.683 --> 00:02:27.734
We zoomed in as much as possible so you
could see her eyes, nose, and mouth.

45
00:02:30.926 --> 00:02:32.580
On that day...

46
00:02:33.657 --> 00:02:36.634
I was a bit annoyed even before
I'd gone to the supermarket.

47
00:02:36.634 --> 00:02:39.597
I hurried out since I thought
that it'd be closing soon.

48
00:02:39.597 --> 00:02:42.284
But Hye Na said that
she wanted to go to the bathroom

49
00:02:42.284 --> 00:02:43.674
as soon as we got in the car.

50
00:02:43.674 --> 00:02:46.830
I barely managed to check out
at the supermarket, and was leaving

51
00:02:46.830 --> 00:02:48.675
but she said she wanted
to use the bathroom again

52
00:02:48.675 --> 00:02:49.895
as soon as the elevator came!

53
00:02:49.895 --> 00:02:51.435
So you hit her with the cart?

54
00:02:51.435 --> 00:02:53.225
It looks a lot worse in the footage.

55
00:02:53.225 --> 00:02:55.588
She only got a few scrapes
and bruises, is all!

56
00:03:05.656 --> 00:03:09.169
On December 12th, you pushed your child
in front of your home, didn't you?

57
00:03:10.588 --> 00:03:12.175
This day was probably the day...

58
00:03:13.277 --> 00:03:16.784
that Hye Na asked me to
buy a new cage for Jjing.

59
00:03:17.479 --> 00:03:20.268
My hands were shaking because I was
worried about my credit card bill

60
00:03:20.268 --> 00:03:21.817
at the end of the month.

61
00:03:21.817 --> 00:03:24.522
But she kept complaining about how
the door of Jjing's cage opened

62
00:03:24.522 --> 00:03:26.740
and said, "What if Jjing runs away?"

63
00:03:36.419 --> 00:03:39.489
Um, if you have some time
by any chance, ma'am...

64
00:03:40.871 --> 00:03:43.032
take care of these for me.

65
00:03:43.032 --> 00:03:47.241
I have to hurry and go to a
funeral by tomorrow morning.

66
00:03:48.135 --> 00:03:49.998
They can't get cold.

67
00:03:49.998 --> 00:03:52.578
And be sure to give them
fresh water in the morning.

68
00:03:53.457 --> 00:03:54.580
Sure.

69
00:03:56.653 --> 00:03:59.242
This is rice, and some side dishes.

70
00:03:59.242 --> 00:04:01.456
And if you open up
the cabinet under the sink

71
00:04:01.456 --> 00:04:02.875
you'll find pots and a rice cooker.

72
00:04:03.375 --> 00:04:05.723
I'm busy, so I'll get going.
Get some rest.

73
00:04:05.723 --> 00:04:08.564
Um, thank you for the food!

74
00:04:36.517 --> 00:04:38.086
I...

75
00:04:40.576 --> 00:04:42.959
hit Hye Na a lot.

76
00:04:44.735 --> 00:04:47.125
I hit her with my hands...

77
00:04:47.807 --> 00:04:50.233
and with whatever else
I could get my hands on.

78
00:04:58.136 --> 00:05:00.634
<i>But Seol Ak never did that.</i>

79
00:05:00.634 --> 00:05:03.151
<i>He protected Hye Na...</i>

80
00:05:03.151 --> 00:05:05.153
<i>and protected me.</i>

81
00:05:05.153 --> 00:05:08.278
There was nobody who had
done that for me before.

82
00:05:09.783 --> 00:05:11.863
The only one who had
done that for me was Seol Ak.

83
00:05:20.795 --> 00:05:22.855
Hello, sir.

84
00:05:22.855 --> 00:05:24.956
That'll be 1,400 won.

85
00:05:33.939 --> 00:05:35.841
Meet me "there" after work.

86
00:05:36.523 --> 00:05:38.725
Have a pleasant day.

87
00:06:16.807 --> 00:06:18.807
Is it okay for you to be drinking coffee?

88
00:06:21.028 --> 00:06:24.204
Seeing your face is making
me a bit nervous, Honey.

89
00:06:24.204 --> 00:06:26.295
So I have to drink coffee
to calm my nerves.

90
00:06:32.187 --> 00:06:34.187
I...

91
00:06:34.802 --> 00:06:36.576
want to get married.

92
00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:40.771
That person doesn't
know about anything.

93
00:06:42.329 --> 00:06:44.230
About Won Hee, I mean.

94
00:06:47.596 --> 00:06:50.396
I really want this to work out for me.

95
00:06:50.396 --> 00:06:52.543
If you're going to get married...

96
00:06:53.970 --> 00:06:55.908
you must have saved up some money.

97
00:06:58.391 --> 00:07:00.233
How much do you need?

98
00:07:01.298 --> 00:07:03.028
You tell me.

99
00:07:04.404 --> 00:07:06.336
Is three million won enough?

100
00:07:13.875 --> 00:07:15.872
It's because I have
to spend a lot...

101
00:07:16.535 --> 00:07:18.783
on the dress and other things.

102
00:07:19.791 --> 00:07:21.456
- Five million?
- Hey.

103
00:07:22.237 --> 00:07:24.201
You're getting married...

104
00:07:25.024 --> 00:07:27.158
and yet, I can't do
anything for you.

105
00:07:28.166 --> 00:07:30.713
But what I can do is take that
money and go away forever.

106
00:07:31.437 --> 00:07:33.485
Also, let me borrow your car.

107
00:07:36.658 --> 00:07:39.458
If I just lend you five million
and my car...

108
00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:43.589
will things really be
over for good between us?

109
00:07:43.589 --> 00:07:44.884
No.

110
00:07:49.927 --> 00:07:52.026
You have to...

111
00:07:52.581 --> 00:07:54.706
guess the correct
answer to this question

112
00:07:54.706 --> 00:07:56.370
for this to all be over.

113
00:07:58.307 --> 00:08:00.418
Why did Won Hee die?

114
00:08:03.661 --> 00:08:05.742
Your son, Won Hee.

115
00:08:06.398 --> 00:08:07.843
Why did he die?

116
00:08:12.821 --> 00:08:14.592
Won Hee...

117
00:08:17.005 --> 00:08:19.756
was playing on the balcony...

118
00:08:21.126 --> 00:08:23.509
while I went out to work...

119
00:08:26.662 --> 00:08:29.211
and climbed up on top of
the clay fermentation jars...

120
00:08:33.054 --> 00:08:35.363
and fell.

121
00:08:35.363 --> 00:08:38.613
That's what you may
be telling others...

122
00:08:39.394 --> 00:08:41.538
but you have to state
the real reason to me.

123
00:08:41.538 --> 00:08:46.062
That it was because
you wanted Won Hee to disappear.

124
00:08:46.062 --> 00:08:47.538
That's not true.

125
00:08:48.567 --> 00:08:51.910
- You did it!
- Because I knew how you felt.

126
00:08:53.557 --> 00:08:55.510
If you still had Won Hee

127
00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:58.222
do you think you'd be
able to get married?

128
00:09:00.408 --> 00:09:02.260
You know?

129
00:09:32.642 --> 00:09:36.876
<i>That was because
you wanted Won Hee to disappear.</i>

130
00:09:36.876 --> 00:09:38.073
<i>That's not true.</i>

131
00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:40.700
<i>You did it!</i>

132
00:09:40.700 --> 00:09:42.658
<i>Because I knew how you felt.</i>

133
00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:08.587
You got back early.

134
00:10:09.248 --> 00:10:10.433
Yes.

135
00:10:12.386 --> 00:10:13.899
Are you considering...

136
00:10:14.566 --> 00:10:17.998
putting your rooftop room up for rent?

137
00:10:17.998 --> 00:10:19.701
Yes.

138
00:10:20.755 --> 00:10:23.203
May we stay there
for just one month?

139
00:10:23.203 --> 00:10:24.437
Yes, you can.

140
00:10:24.437 --> 00:10:26.697
How much should I give you for rent?

141
00:10:29.580 --> 00:10:33.610
The rent for the barber shop
is 1.5 million won per month.

142
00:10:33.610 --> 00:10:36.989
So I'll need at least 200,000 won
from you per month.

143
00:10:37.642 --> 00:10:39.116
That's way too cheap.

144
00:10:39.116 --> 00:10:40.883
You don't have to stay here
if you don't want to.

145
00:10:40.883 --> 00:10:43.741
If I accept a lot of rent from you,
I'll have to do everything you ask.

146
00:10:43.741 --> 00:10:45.902
I don't like having to worry
about things like that.

147
00:10:54.520 --> 00:10:55.945
Here you are.

148
00:11:04.408 --> 00:11:05.725
Hello.

149
00:11:05.725 --> 00:11:08.121
Is the guest staying at Suite 816 here?

150
00:11:08.121 --> 00:11:09.620
Just a moment.

151
00:11:11.567 --> 00:11:13.639
She checked out.

152
00:11:14.326 --> 00:11:15.594
Oh... really?

153
00:11:17.739 --> 00:11:21.529
You're the first person who's
accompanying me as a guardian.

154
00:11:22.318 --> 00:11:26.158
I've never taken someone
to the doctor's office with me before.

155
00:11:26.158 --> 00:11:27.693
Why not?

156
00:11:27.693 --> 00:11:31.736
Mr. Jae Beom, Yi Jin, and everyone
else are so good to you, though.

157
00:11:32.823 --> 00:11:35.759
I've lived like a queen all these years.

158
00:11:35.759 --> 00:11:40.235
I've never lost my dignity
as an actress before.

159
00:11:40.235 --> 00:11:41.599
I know.

160
00:11:41.599 --> 00:11:43.448
You're amazing.

161
00:11:43.448 --> 00:11:45.620
Do you know what my secret to that is?

162
00:11:47.735 --> 00:11:51.624
It's because I'm always
putting on an act.

163
00:11:51.624 --> 00:11:54.599
The role I've been assigned
is that of a queen.

164
00:11:54.599 --> 00:11:55.759
An ice queen.

165
00:11:56.629 --> 00:11:59.572
So I never let myself
reveal my true emotions.

166
00:11:59.572 --> 00:12:03.275
And whenever I ask a favor of someone,
I do it in a demanding way.

167
00:12:03.275 --> 00:12:05.916
And no matter how nice
people are to me

168
00:12:05.916 --> 00:12:08.477
I act as if it's only natural
that they treat me that way.

169
00:12:08.477 --> 00:12:10.759
And if someone
wrongs me in any way

170
00:12:10.759 --> 00:12:13.399
I pay them back tenfold or more,
without remorse.

171
00:12:14.024 --> 00:12:15.884
I've never cried in front of others

172
00:12:15.884 --> 00:12:18.110
without a camera there
to shoot me, either.

173
00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:19.700
Except for one person.

174
00:12:20.222 --> 00:12:22.153
I've only ever cried in front of you.

175
00:12:31.289 --> 00:12:35.645
My husband ran off last year
with some younger woman.

176
00:12:35.645 --> 00:12:37.990
And left me with
nothing but debt.

177
00:12:37.990 --> 00:12:40.575
I know that there are many women

178
00:12:40.575 --> 00:12:44.003
who overcome that and live on
with a strong will, but...

179
00:12:44.688 --> 00:12:46.006
I wasn't one of them.

180
00:12:46.529 --> 00:12:49.870
I was so miserable that I could die,
and I caused a drunk driving accident.

181
00:12:50.494 --> 00:12:52.909
So all the projects that
I had lined up were canceled.

182
00:12:53.503 --> 00:12:56.254
I was considering
just dying, and then...

183
00:12:56.903 --> 00:13:00.034
my agency insisted that
I needed to clean up my image.

184
00:13:00.034 --> 00:13:03.774
So I went to the orphanage, planning
to volunteer there for just one week.

185
00:13:05.134 --> 00:13:07.788
You know that I truly had
a fabulous time there, right?

186
00:13:08.398 --> 00:13:10.331
It was all thanks to you.

187
00:13:19.773 --> 00:13:22.004
<i>And so, I thought...</i>

188
00:13:22.634 --> 00:13:27.047
<i>that I would have nothing to fear
if I had a child like you.</i>

189
00:13:27.047 --> 00:13:29.375
I guess I'm just that kind of person.

190
00:13:29.375 --> 00:13:31.785
I'm too scared to live by myself.

191
00:13:32.971 --> 00:13:34.774
If you really hate this so much

192
00:13:34.774 --> 00:13:37.629
just think of me as the CEO
of your entertainment company.

193
00:13:38.549 --> 00:13:40.565
I'll do my very best

194
00:13:40.565 --> 00:13:43.890
and make sure you're well-fed,
well-dressed, and well-educated.

195
00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:47.139
And I'll be on your side,
no matter what.

196
00:13:57.332 --> 00:14:00.631
I'll take you to your hospital
appointments from now on...

197
00:14:01.337 --> 00:14:03.335
until I leave Korea.

198
00:14:04.374 --> 00:14:05.966
Thanks.

199
00:14:05.966 --> 00:14:08.840
Also, let's take this opportunity
to revise our contract.

200
00:14:08.840 --> 00:14:10.817
I'll be the CEO of your
entertainment company

201
00:14:10.817 --> 00:14:13.042
and you'll be one of my talents.

202
00:14:13.042 --> 00:14:14.717
As for the terms of the contract

203
00:14:14.717 --> 00:14:16.573
we promise to respect one another

204
00:14:16.573 --> 00:14:18.206
and let each other live freely.

205
00:14:18.943 --> 00:14:22.192
If we do that, we may be able
to grow closer together.

206
00:14:24.469 --> 00:14:26.145
Okay, fine!

207
00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:30.166
But you know,
I think you've changed a bit.

208
00:14:30.998 --> 00:14:34.337
When I first put you
in the backseat of my car

209
00:14:34.337 --> 00:14:37.490
and felt as if I'd become
a mother for the first time...

210
00:14:38.716 --> 00:14:40.558
it feels kind of like back then.

211
00:14:42.191 --> 00:14:43.783
Really?

212
00:15:03.629 --> 00:15:06.793
<i>I want to be a barber
when I grow up, too.</i>

213
00:15:06.793 --> 00:15:08.352
<i>Why?</i>

214
00:15:08.352 --> 00:15:11.133
<i>The barber scissors are so pretty.</i>

215
00:15:11.133 --> 00:15:13.683
<i>And they make
such a pleasant sound.</i>

216
00:15:13.683 --> 00:15:16.374
<i>And you look so cool
when you're working.</i>

217
00:15:16.374 --> 00:15:19.702
<i>And the men are powerless
against you, too!</i>

218
00:15:19.702 --> 00:15:21.208
<i>Yoon Bok.</i>

219
00:15:21.208 --> 00:15:25.283
<i>There's no need for you
to become a barber later on.</i>

220
00:15:25.283 --> 00:15:26.816
<i>Why not?</i>

221
00:15:26.816 --> 00:15:29.113
<i>Because you can become one now.</i>

222
00:15:30.275 --> 00:15:32.572
<i>Every barber starts</i>

223
00:15:32.572 --> 00:15:35.549
<i>with sweeping up
the hair on the floor.</i>

224
00:15:38.063 --> 00:15:42.559
<i>And the most important thing is that
you wash other people's hair well.</i>

225
00:15:53.489 --> 00:15:56.363
Doesn't it seem like
there's too much lather in my hair?

226
00:16:03.749 --> 00:16:04.850
Ow!

227
00:16:04.850 --> 00:16:06.791
Ow, that hurts.

228
00:16:06.791 --> 00:16:08.359
Oh?

229
00:16:10.153 --> 00:16:12.035
It's okay, it's okay!

230
00:16:16.956 --> 00:16:19.715
This is the scan that we took last week.

231
00:16:19.715 --> 00:16:23.125
You can see how the
tumor has spread, right?

232
00:16:23.125 --> 00:16:26.587
Don't scare the poor girl.
She may cry.

233
00:16:26.587 --> 00:16:28.730
All doctors talk like this.

234
00:16:28.730 --> 00:16:31.350
And there are some who
even tell you not to get treatment

235
00:16:31.350 --> 00:16:35.558
saying that the people who will die
will die while suffering

236
00:16:35.558 --> 00:16:37.625
and those who will get better
will get better.

237
00:16:37.625 --> 00:16:39.566
And there are tons of different
treatment options nowadays, too.

238
00:16:39.566 --> 00:16:44.413
So, which treatment methods
have you tried so far?

239
00:16:45.319 --> 00:16:47.249
Well...

240
00:16:47.952 --> 00:16:51.262
I bought a pair of sneakers.

241
00:16:52.559 --> 00:16:54.932
And a pair of pants
that match them.

242
00:16:56.611 --> 00:16:59.115
And an overcoat that matches those.

243
00:17:01.450 --> 00:17:04.173
And I don't pick up phone calls
from people I don't like.

244
00:17:04.173 --> 00:17:06.964
And I eat whatever I want,
whenever I want.

245
00:17:07.609 --> 00:17:09.959
So, have you decided to
have chemotherapy?

246
00:17:09.959 --> 00:17:11.375
For now, yeah.

247
00:17:11.375 --> 00:17:15.174
What... made you change your mind?

248
00:17:15.791 --> 00:17:17.933
I'm not scared of dying.

249
00:17:17.933 --> 00:17:21.721
Because I can just do it in my
own style, like everything else I do.

250
00:17:22.695 --> 00:17:25.444
I don't think you'd understand,
Doctor, since you're a man.

251
00:17:25.444 --> 00:17:28.174
But the thing about
being a mother is that...

252
00:17:29.549 --> 00:17:32.000
Being a mother means that

253
00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:34.906
you can't leave behind your children
to just go and die.

254
00:17:34.906 --> 00:17:38.008
I have three children, Doctor.

255
00:17:38.008 --> 00:17:40.984
Two of them grew up in a normal
environment, and are adults.

256
00:17:40.984 --> 00:17:42.837
But she's the only one
among my kids

257
00:17:42.837 --> 00:17:44.680
who stopped growing up
when she was eight

258
00:17:44.680 --> 00:17:47.039
and is the same as she was then.

259
00:17:48.372 --> 00:17:50.450
In my heart, I mean.

260
00:18:06.117 --> 00:18:07.829
Get some rest, Ma'am.

261
00:18:15.477 --> 00:18:17.144
Mom.

262
00:18:18.820 --> 00:18:21.703
You can stop acting now.

263
00:18:22.332 --> 00:18:25.634
Even queens are allowed
to be themselves, a little.

264
00:18:25.634 --> 00:18:28.171
And when it gets too much
for them, they're allowed to retire.

265
00:18:28.826 --> 00:18:31.817
And if you're in pain,
complain about it a bit.

266
00:18:32.457 --> 00:18:33.826
If it weren't for you...

267
00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:39.006
I'd rip all of this off
and leave this place.

268
00:18:39.632 --> 00:18:42.821
I'm good at handling emotional pain.

269
00:18:42.821 --> 00:18:45.465
But I'm really bad with physical pain.

270
00:18:48.228 --> 00:18:49.642
But you know, Mom...

271
00:18:50.592 --> 00:18:54.614
you're not exactly great at dealing
with emotional pain, either.

272
00:18:56.682 --> 00:18:57.942
Yeah.

273
00:19:02.508 --> 00:19:03.815
Mom.

274
00:19:06.375 --> 00:19:07.519
Mom!

275
00:19:09.848 --> 00:19:11.105
Mom!

276
00:19:14.347 --> 00:19:15.871
<i>[Samhwa Barber Shop]</i>

277
00:19:15.871 --> 00:19:18.880
<i>[I'll be right back. If you need me,
please call 010-822-7329]</i>

278
00:19:20.901 --> 00:19:23.443
What are their names?

279
00:19:29.200 --> 00:19:32.451
I named them so long ago, but it's been
so long since I've called them by name.

280
00:19:32.451 --> 00:19:34.324
So I've forgotten their names.

281
00:19:34.324 --> 00:19:36.583
Do these birds know that
they belong to you

282
00:19:36.583 --> 00:19:39.450
even if you don't call them
by their names?

283
00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:41.362
Every time my mom calls my name

284
00:19:41.362 --> 00:19:46.042
I think to myself that
I'm my mom's child.

285
00:19:47.174 --> 00:19:48.784
Really?

286
00:19:49.609 --> 00:19:51.314
Yoon Bok.

287
00:19:51.847 --> 00:19:53.683
That's quite a lovely name.

288
00:19:53.683 --> 00:19:55.178
I know, right?

289
00:19:57.593 --> 00:20:01.723
But, is it okay if I feed them?

290
00:20:01.723 --> 00:20:04.541
I like to feed animals.

291
00:20:05.712 --> 00:20:09.923
I'll entrust the bird-feeding task
to you from now on, then, Yoon Bok.

292
00:20:09.923 --> 00:20:11.336
All right!

293
00:20:11.885 --> 00:20:14.983
What is there in Iceland?

294
00:20:17.184 --> 00:20:20.695
Birds, the ocean, and the sky.

295
00:20:21.540 --> 00:20:24.484
Tons of academic papers
that need to be written.

296
00:20:25.087 --> 00:20:26.465
And...

297
00:20:28.230 --> 00:20:30.826
I have a secret that only I know about.

298
00:20:31.990 --> 00:20:33.717
A man?

299
00:20:34.951 --> 00:20:36.890
Ugh, how boring.

300
00:20:38.038 --> 00:20:41.461
Can't you leave later
if it's not about having a man?

301
00:20:41.461 --> 00:20:43.674
I might die soon, after all.

302
00:20:43.674 --> 00:20:45.507
I'll come back.

303
00:20:46.309 --> 00:20:48.346
I'll be back in six months,
at the very latest.

304
00:20:49.084 --> 00:20:50.613
Or in three months.

305
00:20:50.613 --> 00:20:51.703
Hah.

306
00:20:52.238 --> 00:20:54.892
I have to stay alive
for six whole months, then.

307
00:20:57.234 --> 00:20:58.815
Please.

308
00:21:05.588 --> 00:21:07.387
Doctor Jung?

309
00:21:09.689 --> 00:21:12.031
She's right next to me.

310
00:21:12.031 --> 00:21:13.736
Want me to put her on the line?

311
00:21:14.567 --> 00:21:17.590
Why did you call me if you weren't
going to ask me to put her on the line?

312
00:21:17.590 --> 00:21:20.707
I'm in so much pain right now
because of the chemo.

313
00:21:21.381 --> 00:21:22.790
Doctor Jung...

314
00:21:23.375 --> 00:21:25.438
What a strange fellow.

315
00:21:40.714 --> 00:21:42.630
What about this one?

316
00:21:43.255 --> 00:21:45.519
That's the key for that safe over there.

317
00:21:53.954 --> 00:21:55.444
What about this one?

318
00:21:55.444 --> 00:21:57.516
That's the key for the bird cage.

319
00:21:58.438 --> 00:22:00.978
I'll need to hold on to this one.

320
00:22:00.978 --> 00:22:02.915
Since I'm the one who feeds them.

321
00:22:03.442 --> 00:22:04.748
Sure.

322
00:22:07.127 --> 00:22:08.895
What about this one?

323
00:22:12.395 --> 00:22:13.769
That one is...

324
00:22:14.778 --> 00:22:16.519
I'm not sure about that one.

325
00:22:18.237 --> 00:22:20.130
Let's stop this now.

326
00:22:20.130 --> 00:22:22.558
It'll be bad if
I lose any of these. Okay?

327
00:22:27.343 --> 00:22:30.578
<i>[Safe]</i>

328
00:22:35.661 --> 00:22:39.871
On December 16th,
at Baek Island Mart, did you push a cart

329
00:22:39.871 --> 00:22:41.329
at Kim Hye Na,
your own daughter?

330
00:22:41.329 --> 00:22:42.884
Yes.

331
00:22:43.432 --> 00:22:46.311
Are you at all related to the
disappearance of Kim Hye Na?

332
00:22:46.311 --> 00:22:47.503
No.

333
00:22:47.503 --> 00:22:49.471
Did you kill Kim Hye Na?

334
00:22:50.934 --> 00:22:52.502
No.

335
00:22:57.776 --> 00:23:01.829
Is Lee Seol Ak, the man you live with,
related to Kim Hye Na's disappearance?

336
00:23:01.829 --> 00:23:03.375
No.

337
00:23:05.017 --> 00:23:06.939
<i>Has Lee Seol Ak, the man you live with</i>

338
00:23:06.939 --> 00:23:09.796
<i>ever abused Kim Hye Na?</i>

339
00:23:17.300 --> 00:23:18.605
No.

340
00:23:30.375 --> 00:23:31.818
Honey.

341
00:23:34.648 --> 00:23:35.814
<i>Mister.</i>

342
00:23:35.814 --> 00:23:39.074
<i>Can you hurry and get me the
passport I asked you about earlier?</i>

343
00:23:39.074 --> 00:23:41.148
<i>I'm actually supposed to
meet up with them today.</i>

344
00:23:44.137 --> 00:23:45.701
- What?
- That's not true.

345
00:23:47.731 --> 00:23:50.063
- Hey, watch it!
- Pardon me.

346
00:23:50.063 --> 00:23:51.571
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

347
00:23:52.522 --> 00:23:56.060
Hello! I'm Park Jae Beom,
the person who contacted you earlier.

348
00:23:56.820 --> 00:23:58.630
Oh, I see.

349
00:23:59.993 --> 00:24:01.513
I've heard a lot about you.

350
00:24:01.513 --> 00:24:02.618
I see.

351
00:24:02.618 --> 00:24:04.288
- What's this?
- Well, this is...

352
00:24:04.288 --> 00:24:07.290
I heard that you liked the
30-year-old ones, so I...

353
00:24:07.290 --> 00:24:08.939
Thanks.

354
00:24:09.531 --> 00:24:11.877
But I like single malts more.

355
00:24:15.371 --> 00:24:17.167
What brings you here?

356
00:24:17.167 --> 00:24:19.973
<i>[Samhwa Barber Shop]</i>

357
00:24:23.770 --> 00:24:25.391
I'm sorry for being back so late.

358
00:24:25.391 --> 00:24:26.588
I came straight here.

359
00:24:27.243 --> 00:24:30.342
Yoon Bok didn't cough much today.

360
00:24:30.342 --> 00:24:32.631
She had a good appetite
and played a lot.

361
00:24:32.631 --> 00:24:34.423
She got washed up,
and she's sleeping now.

362
00:24:34.423 --> 00:24:35.759
Thank you.

363
00:24:35.759 --> 00:24:38.355
Thanks to you, I was able to
take my mother to the hospital.

364
00:24:38.355 --> 00:24:41.455
You shouldn't take young children
to hospitals, after all.

365
00:24:42.457 --> 00:24:44.810
Yes. Yoon Bok isn't
completely healthy right now, so...

366
00:24:44.810 --> 00:24:48.323
You shouldn't take healthy children
to hospitals, either.

367
00:24:48.323 --> 00:24:50.877
If you have to go there,
just leave her here and go.

368
00:24:51.772 --> 00:24:53.076
All right.

369
00:24:53.076 --> 00:24:55.136
I'm quite thankful, but...

370
00:24:55.136 --> 00:24:57.148
I don't think that's fair to you.

371
00:24:57.148 --> 00:24:58.586
Then...

372
00:24:59.109 --> 00:25:01.136
do you want to pay me?

373
00:25:02.186 --> 00:25:05.520
You can pay me money
to look after your child.

374
00:25:05.520 --> 00:25:06.945
Shall I do that, then?

375
00:25:06.945 --> 00:25:11.390
I feed her lunch and dinner
and do everything else, too, so...

376
00:25:12.042 --> 00:25:14.563
I'll need at least 5,000 won from you.

377
00:25:16.734 --> 00:25:20.002
Then, I'll give you 5,000 per hour.

378
00:25:21.154 --> 00:25:22.714
Yoon Bok's mother.

379
00:25:22.714 --> 00:25:24.951
Yoon Bok feeds herself
with her own hands

380
00:25:24.951 --> 00:25:26.590
and she can take care
of herself just fine

381
00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:27.693
so how could I accept that

382
00:25:27.693 --> 00:25:29.866
when it's not even that
hard to look after her?

383
00:25:29.866 --> 00:25:32.557
It'll be 5,000 won per day.

384
00:25:32.557 --> 00:25:35.892
Also, I'm looking after
your child because I like her.

385
00:25:35.892 --> 00:25:40.182
If anything, she's doing me a favor
by keeping this old crone company.

386
00:25:40.182 --> 00:25:42.858
I'm so used to eating alone every day.

387
00:25:42.858 --> 00:25:46.371
But now, I hear a cute voice
talking to me as I eat.

388
00:25:46.371 --> 00:25:48.857
And that gives me
more of an appetite.

389
00:25:49.357 --> 00:25:51.326
But still, that's not
nearly enough money.

390
00:25:51.817 --> 00:25:55.107
Is your mother severely ill?

391
00:25:55.760 --> 00:25:57.076
Yes.

392
00:25:57.586 --> 00:25:59.284
She has cancer.

393
00:25:59.284 --> 00:26:00.693
Goodness.

394
00:26:01.224 --> 00:26:04.873
I saw her on a TV show
not too long ago, though.

395
00:26:05.307 --> 00:26:08.704
You... know my mother?

396
00:26:09.230 --> 00:26:12.491
Everyone in this neighborhood knows her.

397
00:26:12.491 --> 00:26:14.980
And I've been living here
for 27 years now.

398
00:26:15.766 --> 00:26:17.050
Um...

399
00:26:17.611 --> 00:26:20.678
I've been meaning to
ask you this, but...

400
00:26:23.171 --> 00:26:27.772
but, 20 years ago,
back when I was a high schooler...

401
00:26:28.378 --> 00:26:32.946
when there was a car accident
right in front of this store...

402
00:26:36.823 --> 00:26:38.624
<i>[Kang Soo Jin]</i>

403
00:26:40.414 --> 00:26:42.513
<i>wasn't the person who treated
my injury at the scene</i>

404
00:26:42.513 --> 00:26:44.338
<i>and called an ambulance for me...</i>

405
00:26:44.900 --> 00:26:46.693
<i>you, Ma'am?</i>

406
00:26:48.618 --> 00:26:50.608
No.

407
00:26:51.240 --> 00:26:54.946
My mother visited you,
saying that she'd like to repay you.

408
00:26:54.946 --> 00:26:57.346
But she said that you insisted
that you weren't the one.

409
00:26:57.346 --> 00:26:59.666
I don't remember that.

410
00:27:04.695 --> 00:27:06.338
I'll need to get some sleep now.

411
00:27:06.338 --> 00:27:09.006
You should go upstairs and
get some rest too, Yoon Bok's mom.

412
00:27:34.590 --> 00:27:36.469
Mom.

413
00:27:37.621 --> 00:27:39.513
You were waiting for me, weren't you?

414
00:27:48.867 --> 00:27:50.741
What's the matter, Yoon Bok?

415
00:27:51.429 --> 00:27:54.190
I came home too late, didn't I?

416
00:27:54.190 --> 00:27:55.827
Did you wait for me
for a long time?

417
00:27:56.323 --> 00:27:57.727
It's because...

418
00:27:58.573 --> 00:28:00.817
I'm so happy.

419
00:28:02.486 --> 00:28:05.457
We don't have to go anywhere...

420
00:28:06.101 --> 00:28:09.387
and we don't have to run.

421
00:28:11.041 --> 00:28:13.875
Because we can just be here...

422
00:28:13.875 --> 00:28:15.801
like this.

423
00:28:21.223 --> 00:28:23.089
We'll...

424
00:28:23.089 --> 00:28:26.330
become even happier, day by day.

425
00:28:27.164 --> 00:28:30.484
Later on, it'll feel natural to be happy.

426
00:28:31.807 --> 00:28:36.048
Later on, you won't even remember...

427
00:28:36.752 --> 00:28:38.653
your old name or your old life.

428
00:28:40.387 --> 00:28:43.040
And when I tell you later on that
you cried because you were so happy

429
00:28:43.040 --> 00:28:45.568
you'll laugh, thinking
that it was ridiculous.

430
00:28:56.368 --> 00:28:58.049
Hey, Yoon Bok.

431
00:29:00.073 --> 00:29:02.426
I think you were right.

432
00:29:05.863 --> 00:29:08.223
The barber shop lady...

433
00:29:09.147 --> 00:29:11.794
seems to be quite a kind person.

434
00:29:15.251 --> 00:29:17.367
We're so lucky...

435
00:29:18.511 --> 00:29:21.336
that we're able to live here.

436
00:29:24.513 --> 00:29:28.311
<i>[Kang Yi Jin]</i>

437
00:29:33.908 --> 00:29:35.657
<i>[Will]</i>

438
00:29:36.057 --> 00:29:40.603
If you have any questions,
the attorney here will take care of them.

439
00:29:40.603 --> 00:29:41.997
I don't like this.

440
00:29:41.997 --> 00:29:44.751
Why are you making these sorts of
preparations, as if you'll be dying?

441
00:29:44.751 --> 00:29:47.803
Shouldn't you be focusing on
your chemo treatment right now?

442
00:29:49.040 --> 00:29:50.105
Yes.

443
00:29:50.105 --> 00:29:54.154
My body may be healthy, but I
periodically work on my own will as well.

444
00:29:54.154 --> 00:29:55.766
It's a completely
normal thing to do.

445
00:29:55.766 --> 00:29:58.298
My real estate will be distributed
equally after being appraised.

446
00:29:58.298 --> 00:30:00.584
As for my shares and gold,
they are to be sold at market price

447
00:30:00.584 --> 00:30:02.060
and the profits are to be
distributed equally.

448
00:30:02.060 --> 00:30:03.338
I'm so, so sorry.

449
00:30:03.338 --> 00:30:05.663
But I have to go now.

450
00:30:06.328 --> 00:30:09.557
I'm fine with anything, Mom.
If you leave me things, I'll be thankful.

451
00:30:09.557 --> 00:30:11.256
But if you don't, that's fine, too.

452
00:30:11.256 --> 00:30:13.712
I'll do exactly as
you all decide today.

453
00:30:13.712 --> 00:30:15.685
That's... okay with you, right?

454
00:30:15.685 --> 00:30:16.897
Of course.

455
00:30:16.897 --> 00:30:18.430
Hurry and go, then.

456
00:30:19.631 --> 00:30:22.012
I'll see you this weekend,
Yi Jin and Soo Jin!

457
00:30:24.375 --> 00:30:27.643
I'm going to give
this house to Yi Jin.

458
00:30:27.643 --> 00:30:29.230
But, Yi Jin.

459
00:30:29.230 --> 00:30:31.503
You can't sell this house until I die.

460
00:30:32.175 --> 00:30:33.713
Why not, Mom?

461
00:30:33.713 --> 00:30:35.904
There needs to be a place
for our family to get together.

462
00:30:35.904 --> 00:30:38.531
It costs so much to
maintain this huge house!

463
00:30:38.531 --> 00:30:41.224
And I might need cash
in a hurry later on!

464
00:30:41.224 --> 00:30:42.326
In exchange...

465
00:30:42.326 --> 00:30:46.467
the furniture in this house, as well
as the decorations and my clothes

466
00:30:46.467 --> 00:30:48.272
will all be yours.

467
00:30:48.988 --> 00:30:53.030
Including your shoes, bags,
and jewelry, too?

468
00:30:53.030 --> 00:30:54.455
Yeah.

469
00:30:54.455 --> 00:30:57.887
Well, I'm the only one
who has your shoe size.

470
00:30:58.637 --> 00:31:00.333
I'm sorry...

471
00:31:00.333 --> 00:31:03.451
but I'd like to give up my right
to inherit anything.

472
00:31:04.371 --> 00:31:06.012
I'm sorry, Soo Jin.

473
00:31:06.012 --> 00:31:08.751
But I won't be leaving you anything.

474
00:31:08.751 --> 00:31:10.743
I was thinking for quite a long time

475
00:31:10.743 --> 00:31:13.086
after the two of us spoke.

476
00:31:13.500 --> 00:31:16.483
I wanted to let you be
as free as possible

477
00:31:16.483 --> 00:31:18.769
so I rewrote my will.

478
00:31:18.769 --> 00:31:21.226
I won't give you
anything at all.

479
00:31:21.226 --> 00:31:25.006
You won't be held down by me anymore.

480
00:31:25.006 --> 00:31:27.645
And you have no obligations
toward me anymore, either.

481
00:31:28.227 --> 00:31:31.336
So go and fly free,
to wherever you wish.

482
00:31:34.253 --> 00:31:36.590
Thank you so much. Really.

483
00:31:39.023 --> 00:31:41.913
But here, it says...

484
00:31:42.486 --> 00:31:44.405
You'll see when you
read it until the end.

485
00:31:44.405 --> 00:31:46.851
Those things aren't
being passed down to you

486
00:31:46.851 --> 00:31:50.382
but to your future children,
Ms. Soo Jin.

487
00:31:50.382 --> 00:31:53.438
I don't want my children to
inherit anything, either.

488
00:31:53.438 --> 00:31:56.711
Just as you are my daughter, yet
I can't force you to do as I wish

489
00:31:56.711 --> 00:32:00.001
I don't think you'll be able to force
your child to do as you wish, either.

490
00:32:00.528 --> 00:32:04.580
I've made it so your child can decide
for themselves when they are of age.

491
00:32:04.580 --> 00:32:07.781
Because there is a possibility
that you may never have a child

492
00:32:07.781 --> 00:32:12.329
your share of the inheritance will be
used to establish a charitable foundation

493
00:32:12.329 --> 00:32:14.522
starting from five years
after Ms. Cha's death.

494
00:32:14.522 --> 00:32:16.807
Ms. Cha has said that she
would like for that foundation

495
00:32:16.807 --> 00:32:20.760
to assist single mothers
and their children.

496
00:32:20.760 --> 00:32:24.644
And she was considering making Ms. Yi Jin
the chairwoman of the foundation.

497
00:32:24.644 --> 00:32:27.279
Yi Jin is most suitable
for running an organization

498
00:32:27.279 --> 00:32:29.189
and she likes children, too.

499
00:32:29.189 --> 00:32:31.583
Do you think I'll be
good at doing that?

500
00:32:31.583 --> 00:32:34.453
I've always wanted to
try doing something like that.

501
00:32:35.054 --> 00:32:36.127
Big Sis.

502
00:32:36.127 --> 00:32:38.156
How old are you turning
this year, again?

503
00:32:38.156 --> 00:32:40.107
38...

504
00:32:40.107 --> 00:32:43.398
Oh, you're definitely still
young enough to have a child!

505
